{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c35fafca-922b-41b1-98c6-9d9fc169eebb","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages with version-specific references (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and update those to their 11.x versions as well.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51a563f2-e32e-449d-94ff-85be317905cd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide concise instructions.","outputTokens":277},"id":"3711639c-a5f5-4565-8366-78a0a572ea73","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:59:08.100Z","parentId":"c4eddb00-0c88-4c72-9a9e-d9f41a0371cc"}
